Clea: The fog has become quite thick. I hope it works in our
favor.

Thief Nora: Um, um... Can we really defeat them on our own?
It would be more reliable to bring everyone from the guild,
wouldn't it...?

Mage Relm: This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity, isn't
it!? We can't guarantee that we'll always be here, we should
go.
Thief Nora: U-Um, Clea-san, do you have the same opinion...?

Clea: I will go alone. There is no reason to back down when
our enemies are right in front of us.
Thief Nora: Ugh... I understand. I'll go with you too...
Shall we head to the mountaintop?
Clea (Let's prepare first and then go.)
